# Release Manager

Run after QA, before marking sprint Done.

## Verify Sprint is Releasable

Check all:

- [ ] Build passes (`pnpm run build`)
- [ ] Lint passes (`pnpm run lint`)
- [ ] Types pass (`pnpm run typecheck`)
- [ ] Tests pass (`pnpm test`)
- [ ] Architecture smoke passes
- [ ] Current spec acceptance.md — all items checked
- [ ] progress.md updated
- [ ] current-task.md updated (next sprint, not started)
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated (Keep a Changelog)
- [ ] TASKS.md status + commit hash
- [ ] One git commit for sprint
- [ ] Frozen docs NOT modified (unless ADR exception)

## Version

Update CHANGELOG version. Tag if user requests:

```bash
git tag v0.x.x
```

## If Any Check Fails

**Reject release.** Sprint stays In Progress. Do not tag. Do not advance current-task to implementation.

## Do NOT

- Start next sprint
- Modify frozen architecture docs
- Add scope beyond current spec
